Data is available from PhysioNet MIMIC-III Clinical Database:
Johnson, A., Pollard, T., & Mark, R. (2016). MIMIC-III Clinical Database (version 1.4). PhysioNet. RRID:SCR_007345. https://doi.org/10.13026/C2XW26

Data preprocessing is available from github repo: caml-mimic
from paper:Explainable Prediction of Medical Codes from Clinical Text

Pre-trained word embedding is available from huggingface garyw/clinical-embeddings-300d-w2v-oa-available
Flamholz ZN, Crane-Droesch A, Ungar LH, Weissman GE. Word embeddings trained on published case reports are lightweight, effective for clinical tasks, and free of protected health information. J Biomed Inform. 2022 Jan;125:103971. doi: 10.1016/j.jbi.2021.103971. Epub 2021 Dec 14. PMID: 34920127; PMCID: PMC8766939.

Filtration and generation following Not Fully Synthetic: LLM-based Hybrid Approaches Towards Privacy-Preserving Clinical Note Sharing
Rahman Sarkar A, Chuang YS, Jiang X, Mohammed N. Not Fully Synthetic: LLM-based Hybrid Approaches Towards Privacy-Preserving Clinical Note Sharing. AMIA Jt Summits Transl Sci Proc. 2025 Jun 10;2025:441-450. PMID: 40502247; PMCID: PMC12150723.

Data is not permitted to be shared as it requires credentialed access.
The others are not included because of the limitation of the size of the files, but they can be found online.


The model can be ran by:
python fusiondp-text.py \
                              --epochs 20 \
                              --batch_size 256 \
                              --lr 0.2 \
                              --epsilon 5.0 \
                              --max_grad_norm 1.0 \
                              --mode "fusiondp" \
                              --alpha 0.5 \
                              --beta 0.5